411\u304b\u3044\u306e\u30d0\u30ba\u308b\u5bb6\u65cf|publisher=ytv|access-date=May 23, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401065823/https://www.ytv.co.jp/buzz/story/|archive-date=April 1, 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| Japanese drama / episode 7\n|-\n|''Songs of Tokyo''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhk.or.jp/songsoftokyo/#program-overview|title=SONGS OF TOKYO Festival 2019|date=August 13, 2019|website=NHK|access-date=August 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kyarystaff/status/1162337311570288641|title=Tweet about the show|date=August 13, 2019|website=Twitter|access-date=August 19, 2019}}{{Primary source inline|date=February 2020}}</ref>\n|Herself\n|[[NHK World]]\n|Japanese music and culture / episode 5\n|-\n|}\n\n===Website===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010\u20132012\n| ''Kyary Pamyu Pamyu no Way-Way Channel''\n| Herself/ Host\n| Niconico\n| [[Niconico|Niconico Douga]] channel\n|-\n| 2012\u20132013\n| ''Dam Channel!''\n| Herself/ MC\n| Club Dam<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clubdam.com/app/dam/page.do?type=dam&source=index&subType=damchannel|title=DAMCHANNEL}}</ref>\n| Karaoke system program\n|-\n| 2012\u20132013\n| ''Catherine the Thirteenth''\n| Herself / Host\n| [[Kansai Telecasting Corporation|Kansai TV]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/catherine3ch|title=Catherine 13th|publisher=[[Kansai Telecasting Corporation]]}}</ref>\n| YouTube channel/ Japanese variety show\n|-\n| 2012\u2013present\n| ''Harajuku Kawaii!! TV''\n| Herself\n| ''Harajuku Kawaii!! TV''<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/user/HARAJUKUKAWAiiTV HARAJUKUKAWAii!! TV Channel].</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://asbs.jp/|title=Harajuku Kawaii!! Style|publisher=Asbs.jp|accessdate=July 20, 2014}}</ref>\n| YouTube channel/ blog\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n| ''Kyary Pamyu Pamyu Goes Pop''\n| Herself\n| ''The EY Exhibition: The World Goes Pop''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tate.org.uk/whats-on/tate-modern/exhibition/ey-exhibition-world-goes-pop|title=The EY Exhibition: The World Goes Pop|publisher=London TATE MODERN|accessdate=November 30, 2015}}</ref>\n| Video Collab at Art Exhibition\n|}\n\n===Radio===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2012\u20132015\n| ''Kyary Pamyu Pamyu Way Way Radio!''\n| Herself/ Host\n| [[TBS Radio & Communications|TBS]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tbsradio.jp/pamyu/|title=TBS RADIO 954 kHz \u2502 \u304d\u3083\u308a\u30fc\u3071\u307f\u3085\u3071\u307f\u3085\u306e\u30a6\u30a7\u30a4\u30a6\u30a7\u30a4\u30ec\u30c7\u30a3\u30aa}}</ref>\n| Part of the radio program \"Kakiiin\"\n|-\n| 2015\u20132018\n| ''Kyary Locks!''\n| Herself/ Host\n| [[Tokyo FM|TFM]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tfm.co.jp/lock/kyary/|title=Kyary LOCKS!\u2502\u304d\u3083\u308a\u30fcLOCKS!}}</ref>\n| Part of the radio program \"School of Lock!\", Monthly \u2013 Thursdays\n|-\n| 2019\u2013present\n| ''Kyary Pamyu Pamyu no Nantoka Pan Pan Radio''\n| Herself/ Host\n| [[Japan FM Network|JFN]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://park.gsj.mobi/program/show/43953|title=Kyary no Nantoka Pan Pan Radio\u2502\u304d\u3083\u308a\u30fc\u3071\u307f\u3085\u3071\u307f\u3085\u306e\u3000\u306a\u3093\u3068\u304b\u3071\u3093\u3071\u3093\u30e9\u30b8\u30aa}}</ref>\n| Co-Mc Masaru Ikeda\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Kyary Pamyu Pamyu discography}}\n* ''[[Pamyu Pamyu Revolution]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Nanda Collection]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[Pika Pika Fantajin]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Japamyu]]'' (2018)\n\n==Tours==\n;Japan tours\n* Pamyu Pamyu Revolution Tour (2012)\n* Nanda Collection Tour: Kyary Pamyu Pamyu's Universal Theater (2013)\n* Pika Pika Fantajin Tour: Kyary Pamyu Pamyu no Kumo no Ue no Heaven's Door (2014)\n* Kyary Pamyu Pamyu's Colorful Panic Toy Box (2014)\n* Crazy Party Night Tour (2016)\n* Special DJ  \u00d7 Live ZEPP Tour 2016: YSTK \u00d7 KPP (2016)\n* KPP Japan Iyahoi Tour (2017)\n* Japamyu Hall Tour 2018: Cherry Martini of Stardust (2018)\n* Ono no Kuni Live Tour (2019)\n* Yasutaka Nakata x Kyary Pamyu Pamyu Presents SPECIAL DJ & LIVE TOUR: YSTK\u00d7KPP LIVE TOUR (2020)\n* Kyary Pamyu Pamyu Kamaitachi TOUR (2020 - canceled)\n\n;World tours\n* [[100%KPP World Tour]] (2013)\n* [[Nanda Collection World Tour]] (2014)\n* Five Years Monster World Tour (2016)\n* The Spooky Obakeyashiki: Pumpkins Strike Back (2017\u201318)\n* Kyary Pamyu Pamyu LIVE TOUR (2020)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2011\n| Best Styling Award 2011\n| Artist\n| Herself\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Antville Music Video Awards\n| Most Fun \n| rowspan=\"2\" | \"[[Pon Pon Pon]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Art Direction \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2012\n| Music Jacket Award\n| Grand Prix\n| ''[[Moshi Moshi Harajuku]]''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Space Shower Music Video Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Special Award\n| rowspan=\"6\" | Herself\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Wired Japan Grand Prix\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Japan Record Awards]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Vogue Japan Women of the Year\n| Stylist\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Video Music Awards Japan]]\n| Best New Artist\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| Best Dressed Award\n| International\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"11\" | 2013\n| [[CD Shop Awards]]\n| The CD Shop Grand Prix\n| ''[[Pamyu Pamyu Revolution]]''\n| style=\"background:lightsteelblue;text-align:center\"|2nd Place\n|-\n| Space Shower Music Video Awards\n| Video of the Year\n| \"[[Tsukematsukeru]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Rekochoku Best March Month Music Award\n| Download (Single)\n| rowspan=\"2\"|\"[[Ninjari Bang Bang]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Ring Song\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | MTV Video Music Awards Japan\n| Best Pop Video\n| rowspan=\"2\" | \"[[Fashion Monster]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Karaoke Song\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Fuse TV]]<ref name=\"Fuse TV Best New Artist Poll\"/><ref name=\"allkpop.com\"/>\