\u6700\u3082\u95a2\u4fc2\u6027\u3092 \u7bc9\u3044\u3066\u304d\u305f\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8\u306b\u611f\u8b1d\u3092\u8fbc\u3081\u3066\u6388\u4e0e\u3059\u308b\u8cde\u3002\u304d\u3083\u308a\u30fc\u3071\u307f\u3085\u3071\u307f\u3085|access-date=May 22, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170308050106/https://tokyomusicodyssey.jp/awards/winners/#friends|archive-date=March 8, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017 MTV Europe Music Awards\n| Best Japanese Act\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2018\n| Space Shower Music Video Awards\n| Best Female Artist\n| {{nom}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://awards.spaceshower.jp/2018/nominees/|title=SPACE SHOWER MUSIC AWARDS 2018 NOMINEES}}</ref>\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2019\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Space Shower Music Video Awards\n| Best Female Artist\n| {{nom}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://awards.spaceshower.jp/2019/nominees/|title=SPACE SHOWER MUSIC AWARDS 2019 NOMINEES}}</ref>\n|-\n|-\n| Best Art Direction Video\n|\"Oto no Kuni\"\n| {{win}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://awards.spaceshower.jp/2019/winners/|title=SPACE SHOWER MUSIC AWARDS 2019 WINNERS}}</ref>\n|-\n|-\n|}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{Citation|author=Caroline Charonplop Kyarypamyupamyu|date=August 18, 2011|title=Oh! My God!! Harajuku Girl|publisher=[[Poplar Publishing]]|edition=Hardcover|location=Tokyo|language=Japanese|isbn=978-4-591-12542-7|url=http://www.poplar.co.jp/shop/shosai.php?shosekicode=80007570|ref={{Harvid|KPP|2011}}}}\n* {{Citation|author=Kyary Pamyu Pamyu|date=June 21, 2012|title=Oh! My God!! Harajuku Girl|publisher=[[Poplar Publishing]]|edition=Paperback Bunko|series=Poplar Bunko|location=Tokyo|language=Japanese|isbn=978-4-591-13045-2|url=http://www.poplar.co.jp/shop/shosai.php?shosekicode=81011940|ref={{Harvid|KPP|2012b}}}}\n* {{Citation|author1=Caroline Charonplop Kyary Pamyu Pamyu|others=Yasumasa Yonehara (Photographer)|date=July 29, 2011|title=Harajuku Kawaii!!!! girls|publisher=Gain|location=Nagoya, Japan|language=Japanese|series=Gain mook|isbn=978-4-901